	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=175669><span id= >Stoutoak</span></a><br><span id=notbold>52 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.07]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p> Good info from Darg, just throwing my 2 cents in because I just purchased one recently on 7th hammer, cost me 25k.&nbsp;&nbsp;I know it seems like alot, and it is/was for me, but when you think about it, you are talking about a 263pt DD mana free, castable over and over again!!  8 second cast time, but even with only the 44th lvl togor's slow, I can easily cast it between the mobs swing's at me without getting interrupted.  And even when I get hit, 4 times outta 5 I don't get interrupted.  If you wanna go psycho, AA points into spell casting fury effects the bracer, so you can get mana free crits!! &lt;drool&gt;<br>   As far as the camp goes, fairly sure you have 6 static spawns in the crypt itself, the two crypt keeper guardians, and the the four named/placeholders in the actual crypts.  Then there are maybe 2-3 wanderers that walk through there, the ghoulknights.  I think a group of 4 could camp it with ease if you are just going for loot, because once broken the spawns are quite easy imo, for 4 people 55+.  A rogue, shaman, tank and just about any other class could handle it easy.  Don't really even think a chanter is necessary if the puller is 59+.<br>  Reason I believe it is still a pricey item is that not only is it a rare drop, but fewer and fewer people frequent Sebillis, unless you are AE grouping.  Its pretty much bring your own group. If anyone on the 7th wants to venture there, look me up.... always eager to hit the crypt.  Bracer for the shammie, cloak for me!!! hehe<br><br>Stoutoak<br>60 Cleric, 7th</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
